The paper deals with combinatorial problems related to graph theory and constraint satisfaction, which are typically covered by the arXiv sub-categories cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The focus on the Dichotomy Conjecture and the LIST MATRIX PARTITION problem suggests cs.CC and cs.DM as the most likely categories, while the use of combinatorial techniques and the 3-COMPATIBLE COLOURING problem may also make cs.CG, cs.DS, and cs.GT relevant.
